brewery.brewery_description: Founded in the little coastal Queensland town of Bargara. We all love Bargara and Love beer, so we felt impelled to share our passion on what a real brewing company should represent. We want to do good, not just taste good. We want to use the best to produce the best. We want craft beer drinking to be a culture of authenticity, mateship, innovation, respect, awareness and appreciation.

beer.beer_description: A Belgian Style ale that's very pale and cloudy in appearance due to it being partially unfiltered and the high level of wheat that's used in the mash. Phat Heffa exhibits spiced notes of banana, cloves and orange peel in the back ground. The crispness and slight twang comes from the wheat and the lively level of carbonation. This is one style that many brewers in the US have taken a liking to and have done a very good job of staying to style, Phat Heffa is our Australian take on the style. Sometimes served with a lemon, but if you truly want to enjoy the untainted subtleties of this style you'll ask for yours without one.

beer.beer_description: A refreshing Bright Lager with a smooth, yet crisp, finish. Australian bittering hops are augmented with German aroma varieties, including Hallertau and Perle, to add a European twist to this perfectly constructed beer. The easy drinking nature of Bargara Brewing Company’s Thirsty Turtle makes it the perfect companion to a lazy Sunday session with snack’s in the shade of an old fig tree looking out over the ocean.

A full bodied malt based Ginger beer in which the RedX malt exhibits a rich sweetness with a smooth creamy finish. The ginger builds on the pallet to give a warm zesty finish of lemon and fresh baked ginger in the aroma. The Ginja Ninja is a unique beer utilising a healthy dose locally grown "Bunda Ginga" .Equally refreshing straight up or on ice.
